{"word":"κακία","slug":"κακία","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κακία</b></el> <el>(κᾰκία, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κακός'><el>κακός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>badness</i> in quality, <a href='S:opposed to'>opp. to</a> <el>ἀρετή</el> <i>(excellence)</i>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—<a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <el>κακίαι</el> <i>defects</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>cowardice, sloth</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>moral badness, wickedness, vice</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>ill-repute</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><i>evil</i> suffered, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}